show_title: Ringo in the Bracket, Skycastle in the Clouds: GM Farcaster ep291
text:
i think skycastle is a great concept. 

it helps focus liquidity. 

cabal-ing becomes somewhat more public and transparent. 

and there are clearly some very strong and solid names backing this project. 

for all these reasons, i've bought some $SKY - both on my fc and non-doxxed wallets. 

that said, i'd be remiss in not mentioning my disappointment in the lack of diversity in the partner network.

forgive me if i'm mistaken here, but as far as i can tell, Debbie is either among - or the only - woman on this Partner list.

if the expertise offered by this group is "strategy, PMF, product build, comms, GTM, brand, UX, and tokenomics" then i can assure you there are plenty of bright, experienced women on base and farcaster who fit the mold.

i could tag some of them here but the list would honestly be too long.

i also wanna be really clear - i personally know a lot of the people associated with skycastle to be terrific, bright and inclusive individuals. so this isn't run-of-the-mill FUD aimed to tear them down.

i just think the optics here matters. 

and i'm not sure if it was intentional or an oversight, but either way i'm disappointed that a project with so much promise and visibility missed the opportunity to set a stronger example on diversity and representation. 

especially given how central inclusivity is to building long-lasting communities.

cast.text:
Our network is anchored by 30 Partners bringing expertise across tokens, product, engineering, marketing, distribution, community & capital. 

Beyond that, we expand to a Council of 64, invited by Partners & aligned via shared incentives to broaden reach, perspective & support.

Including our two founders & four senior advisors, the network extends 100 deep ‚Äì all working for & committed to the success of your next project.

I don't believe in quotas. And I believe that diversity is more than external appearance, gender or otherwise. 

But this is a real short-sighted failing. I'm guilty, and I'm sorry.

I will speak for myself and say that I'll strive to do better here.

ùóñùóÆùóØùóÆùóπ ùóîùó∞ùó∞ùòÇùòÄùóÆùòÅùó∂ùóºùóªùòÄ
Cabal in modern parlance is just a midcurve word for what's referred to as mafias (Paypal, YC, etc.) in SV. 

Short of a solo-founder doing a fair-market launch (like $NATIVE), this will be a perennial barb. 

That said, a true cabal would not be as visible as this group is. You know who's in it. You know how it works. The docs are available on day one. It's a token on the open-market. 

Yes, it took pre-meditated coordination and planning that didn't involve posting every decision to the feed (see: DAOs, Rainbow's M&A department, etc.).

But that's how the real world works. 

ùóßùóµùó≤ ùó°ùóîùó© ùó†ùóºùó±ùó≤ùóπ
Very fair sets of questions here. My assessment in joining $SKY was primarily around this. My answer? The NAV model, especially when tokenized, aligns our incentives with founders and token-holders from Day Zero. 

It puts the onus on us to a) pick great projects with plenty of room to grow and move the needle for our entire space and b) help add value to those projects through effort and elbow grease.

show_title: Ringo in the Bracket, Skycastle in the Clouds: GM Farcaster ep291
text:
excited to onboard @javabu.eth to build and grow a home base for /politics on cura. 

we're going to support him in curating the best politics related conversations/feed, onboard net new users and enable crypto native incentives and mini apps for the /politics channel.

üëÄ ready to take on giants

cast.text:
Farcaster doesn‚Äôt really work for channels ‚Äî good posts get lost, notifications don‚Äôt land, and it‚Äôs hard to track who‚Äôs contributing. And Base? It doesn‚Äôt even support channels.

That‚Äôs why /politics now is working to fully integrate with @cura. What does that mean for you?

1. Top posts stay pinned and curated ‚Äî plus we‚Äôll be rewarding curated content.
2. Notifications make sure you don‚Äôt miss updates or replies.
3. Contributors get real recognition with leaderboards, recurring $Buster drops, and ways to earn.
4. Everything lives in one place: posting, following, rewards, and curation.
5. Our content spreads beyond Cura too ‚Äî showing up on Farcaster, Base, and X.

You can open the /politics home base inside the mini apps on Farcaster and Base. But for the full experience, go straight to cura.network/politics (web) or download the iOS app https://apps.apple.com/us/developer/karma3-labs/id1795955093
